The paper focuses on the use of deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), to analyze tongue images and construct herbal prescriptions. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to model the therapy of Chinese doctors, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of mobile medical systems also suggests a potential application in multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
